In a statement from June 20, 2009, the President of the United States addressed the situation in Iran. He expressed condolences for the lives lost and called on the Iranian government to cease all violent actions against its own people. The President emphasized the importance of respecting the universal rights to assembly and free speech. He stated that suppressing ideas does not make them disappear and that the Iranian people will ultimately judge their own government's actions. The President urged the Iranian government to govern through consent and not coercion if it wants to gain the respect of the international community. He referenced Martin Luther King's quote about the arc of the moral universe bending towards justice and expressed belief in that truth. The President stated that the international community is witnessing the Iranian people's belief in this truth and will continue to bear witness.